# Cursor rules for this Second Brain vault.
# Copy to vault root as `.cursorrules`.

## What this vault is
A personal knowledge vault — markdown files organized by semantic folder
(daily/, weekly/, projects/, references/, inbox/, research-skill-graph/).
Every file has YAML frontmatter with a `type:` field.

## Editing rules

- Match section structure and tone of existing files in the same folder
- Never reorder or remove frontmatter keys
- Use `_templates/*.md` when creating new files
- Filenames: kebab-case, meaningful slug
- Dated updates in project files go AT THE END (most recent last)

## Dates

Convert relative dates ("last Tuesday", "next week") to absolute YYYY-MM-DD
before writing them into files.

## Git

This vault is a git repo. Suggest commits with terse content-describing
messages (not "update file"). Never push without explicit approval.

## Braindump pattern

When I ask you to log work to my second brain:
1. Identify which `projects/*.md` file the work belongs to (ask if unclear)
2. Read that file to learn its house style
3. Add a new `## Section (YYYY-MM-DD)` block BEFORE `## Lessons Learned`
4. Use bullet points with `**bold**` key terms
5. Keep it terse — bullets not paragraphs

## What to avoid

- Don't delete content during "cleanup" without showing exactly what you'd
  delete first
- Don't paraphrase existing content — summarize only at section boundaries
- Don't generate content-free preambles ("I'll update the file now") — just do it
